# WPF Development Guidelines

## XAML Structure
- Use consistent naming conventions for UI elements
- Implement proper data binding for MVVM pattern
- Use resource dictionaries for consistent styling
- Ensure accessibility with proper labels and descriptions

## Code-Behind Patterns
- Keep code-behind minimal, delegate logic to services
- Use async/await for network operations
- Implement proper error handling and user feedback
- Use INotifyPropertyChanged for data binding updates

## UI/UX Guidelines
- Design child-friendly interface for Time Limit App
- Create professional, easy-to-use interface for Admin App
- Use clear visual indicators for time remaining
- Implement responsive design for different screen sizes
- Provide clear feedback for all user actions

## Security Considerations
- Implement proper authentication for Admin App
- Secure communication between components
- Prevent unauthorized access to time limit settings
- Log all administrative actions for audit purposes

## File Organization
- Separate UI logic from business logic
- Use services for external communication
- Implement proper dependency injection
- Follow MVVM pattern for maintainable code
